{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Many times the URL presented to the user within a browser may need to be customized. For example, a custom query string argument needs to be appended to the URL, such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"idp"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"login_hint"},{"type":"text","text":", or other parameters. These may be used by the Sign In Widget to determine how to present the UI to your user. Alternatively, other advanced use-cases may require more complex configuration of the URL."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since this URL is typically generated at runtime, APIs are needed to give you the capability to configure this URL."}]},{"anchor":"Query-String-Parameters","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Query String Parameters"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The simplest approach to customizing your authorization URL is adding additional parameters to the query string. These values can be supplied to the initializer, either through the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/WebAuthenticationUI\/documentation\/WebAuthenticationUI\/WebAuthentication\/init(issuer:clientId:scopes:responseType:redirectUri:logoutRedirectUri:additionalParameters:)"},{"type":"text","text":" initializer, or through the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Okta.plist"},{"type":"text","text":" configuration format (see "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/WebAuthenticationUI\/documentation\/WebAuthenticationUI\/ConfiguringYourClient"},{"type":"text","text":" for more information)."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let auth = WebAuthentication(issuer: issuer,","                             clientId: clientId,","                             scopes: \"openid profile offline_access\",","                             redirectUri: redirectUri,","                             additionalParameters: [ \"idp\": myIdpString ])","let token = try await auth.signIn()"]},{"anchor":"Customizing-the-Authorization-URL-through-Delegation","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Customizing the Authorization URL through Delegation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/WebAuthenticationUI\/documentation\/WebAuthenticationUI\/WebAuthentication"},{"type":"text","text":" class exposes the underlying OAuth2 flow through the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/WebAuthenticationUI\/documentation\/WebAuthenticationUI\/WebAuthentication\/signInFlow"},{"type":"text","text":" property. The authentication flows, defined within the OktaOAuth2 SDK, all support a multicast delegate mechanism to notify other parts of the SDK as well as your application of important events."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your code conforms to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AuthorizationCodeFlowDelegate"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol, and implements the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"authentication(flow:customizeUrl:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method, you can alter the URL before it is loaded in the browser."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let auth = try WebAuthentication()","auth.add(delegate: self)","","let token = try await auth.signIn()"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Elsewhere in your code, in the class that conforms to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AuthorizationCodeFlowDelegate"},{"type":"text","text":", you can implement the appropriate methods to customize the URL:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func authentication<Flow: AuthorizationCodeFlow>(","    flow: Flow,","    customizeUrl urlComponents: inout URLComponents)","{","    urlComponents.queryItems?.append(URLQueryItem(name: \"idp\", value: myIdpString))","    urlComponents.fragment = \"recover\"","}"]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":2,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/webauthenticationui\/customizingauthorizationurl"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WebAuthenticationUI\/documentation\/WebAuthenticationUI\/CustomizingAuthorizationURL","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Features and APIs to enable customization of the authorization URL."}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Customizing the Authorization URL","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"WebAuthenticationUI"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WebAuthenticationUI\/documentation\/WebAuthenticationUI"]]},"references":{"doc://WebAuthenticationUI/documentation/WebAuthenticationUI/WebAuthentication/signInFlow":{"role":"symbol","title":"signInFlow","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"let"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"signInFlow"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"AuthorizationCodeFlow","preciseIdentifier":"s:10OktaOAuth221AuthorizationCodeFlowC"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The underlying OAuth2 flow that implements the authentication behavior."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WebAuthenticationUI\/documentation\/WebAuthenticationUI\/WebAuthentication\/signInFlow","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/webauthenticationui\/webauthentication\/signinflow"},"doc://WebAuthenticationUI/documentation/WebAuthenticationUI/WebAuthentication/init(issuer:clientId:scopes:responseType:redirectUri:logoutRedirectUri:additionalParameters:)":{"role":"symbol","title":"init(issuer:clientId:scopes:responseType:redirectUri:logoutRedirectUri:additionalParameters:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"convenience"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"issuer"},{"ki